#: L1_MusicReading/L1_MusicReading.cpp:53
msgid "Note symbols"
msgstr "Los símbolos para las notas"

#: L1_MusicReading/L1_MusicReading.cpp:54
msgid "We have learn that the vertical position of a note on the staff determines its pitch. The duration of the note (that, is the duration of its sound) is indicated by using different types of signs for the notes, so each note sign corresponds to a different duration. The following picture shows the different types of notes and their names:"
msgstr "Sabemos que la posición vertical de una nota en el pentagrama determina su sonido. La duración de la nota, esto es, el tiempo que debe durar el sonido, se indica utilizando símbolos distintos para las diferentes duraciones de las notas. La siguiente figura muestra los distintos tipos de notas y sus nombres:"

#: L1_MusicReading/L1_MusicReading.cpp:55
msgid "Whole"
msgstr "Redonda"

#: L1_MusicReading/L1_MusicReading.cpp:56
msgid "Half"
msgstr "Blanca"

#: L1_MusicReading/L1_MusicReading.cpp:57
msgid "Quarter"
msgstr "Negra"

#: L1_MusicReading/L1_MusicReading.cpp:58
msgid "Eight"
msgstr "Corchea"

#: L1_MusicReading/L1_MusicReading.cpp:59
